## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 1 (systemic — affects 7/10 tests) |
| **Medium** | 1 |
| **Low** | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is invoked, achieving high line coverage, but almost nothing is actually verified. Bugs in `UpdatePrice`, `ApplyBulkDiscount`, `RemoveProduct`, `ImportFromCsv`, and `GetProductCount` would never be caught.

---

### 🔴 Critical: Coverage Touching / No Meaningful Assertions

**Pattern**: 7 of 10 tests either have **zero assertions** or only assert `IsNotNull` on a result that can never be null (an empty `List<T>` or an empty `string` still passes `IsNotNull`).

| Test Method | Problem |
|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` (L17-21) | No assertion at all — doesn't verify the product was stored |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33-36) | No assertion — never checks the price actually changed |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (L39-43) | No assertion — never checks the product was removed |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (L63-66) | No assertion — doesn't check the count value |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L69-74) | No assertion — never verifies discounted prices |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L85-88) | No assertion — never verifies the product was imported |
| `SearchProducts_Works` (L47-52) | `Assert.IsNotNull` on a `List<T>` (never null) — doesn't verify correct item returned |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55-60) | Same — `IsNotNull` on list, doesn't verify contents |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` (L78-82) | `IsNotNull` on `string` — doesn't verify CSV content |

**Why this is dangerous**: A `UpdatePrice` implementation that silently does nothing would pass. A `RemoveProduct` that no-ops would pass. You get 95% coverage with 0% defect detection.

**Concrete fixes** (examples for the most impactful tests):

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_UpdatesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_ProductNoLongerRetrievable()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}

